cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about RGBD semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel Attention Complementary Network (ACNet) that selectively gathers features from RGB and depth branches, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of ResNet50, which is a popular deep learning architecture for computer vision tasks, indicating that cs.MM (Multimedia) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, since RGBD semantic segmentation can be applied in robotics, cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible sub-category as well.
